benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/tags - Add tags to bundle

covered: POST Valid Payload: Scenarios TC01, TC03, TC04, TC05 demonstrate successful creation of tag resources with valid payloads (single and multiple tags).
Optional Headers: TC02 covers usage of optional headers X-Killbill-Reason and X-Killbill-Comment.
Empty Payload: TC07 validates that an empty tag list results in 201 with no changes.
Invalid Input Variants: TC08, TC09, TC10, TC11, TC12, TC15, TC18 cover malformed JSON, non-array bodies, missing bodies, extra fields, and invalid UUIDs.
Missing/Invalid Headers: TC13 ensures missing header handling; TC16 covers unauthorized access scenarios.
Bundle ID Validation: TC08 (invalid bundleId format) and TC09 (non-existent bundle) address bundle id validation.
Error Handling: TC17 (503) and TC22 (504) cover service unavailability and slow backend conditions.
Recovery/Idempotency: TC19 demonstrates recovery from transient failures and retry behavior.
Payload Size Scenarios: TC20 (maximum payload) and TC21 (payload too large) address size boundaries.
Duplication Handling: TC26 ensures no duplicates appear in the response when duplicates are supplied.
Integration: TC27 and TC28 verify GET and cross-service data consistency after POST.
Accessibility: TC29 addresses API documentation accessibility.
Performance: TC24 and TC25 cover normal and peak load performance of the endpoint.
gaps: Rate Limiting: No dedicated tests for rate limiting or throttling on this POST endpoint.
Caching Behavior: No tests for caching headers or GET-cache-related semantics stemming from POST operations.
403 Forbidden Coverage: Only 401 for missing/invalid token is tested; explicit 403 for insufficient permissions is not covered.
Internal Server Error: No test explicitly simulates 500 Internal Server Error.
Content-Type/Accept Edge Cases: Variations like incorrect Content-Type or Accept headers are not tested.
Additional edge-case validation: Additional negative tests for payload structure beyond defined UUIDs could be explored.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting/throttling tests for POST /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/tags to validate resilience under high load.
Add 403 Forbidden scenarios to cover insufficient permissions in addition to missing/invalid tokens.
Add 500 Internal Server Error scenario tests to complete server-error coverage.
Add tests around caching headers and GET caching behavior to validate end-to-end caching semantics.
Introduce tests for Content-Type and Accept header variations and invalid header combinations.
Expand negative boundary tests for payload shape and security checks (e.g., more injection patterns).
